    {
        "content": "<p>Firstly, instead of using <code>tsum</code> (topological sum) you can just use regular sum (<code>∑</code> instead of <code>∑'</code>). This allows you to use the lemma <code>integral_finset_sum</code>. Secondly you need to assume the functions are integrable, otherwise it won't necessarily be true.</p>",
        "id": 562329842,
        "sender_full_name": "David Ledvinka",
        "timestamp": 1765136152
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah I used <code>∑'</code> so that I could apply <code>integral_tsum_of_summable_integral_norm</code>, which operates on <code>∑'</code> specifically, not <code>∑</code>. is there another function that's equivalent to <code>integral_tsum_...</code> but for  <code>∑</code>?</p>",
        "id": 562329954,
        "sender_full_name": "Becker A.",
        "timestamp": 1765136269
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sorry I edited my message to include it right after I posted. Its <code>integral_finset_sum</code>. Note tsum is for possibly infinite sum, this is why you get the extra <code>Summability</code>goal that requires you to show the sum converges.</p>",
        "id": 562330013,
        "sender_full_name": "David Ledvinka",
        "timestamp": 1765136340
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note that you don't need independence for linearity of the expectation.</p>",
        "id": 562330301,
        "sender_full_name": "Rémy Degenne",
        "timestamp": 1765136612
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"223948\">David Ledvinka</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/prob.20and.20stats.20e.2Eg.2E.20in.20Lean4.20-.20linearity.20of.20expectation/near/562330013\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>tsum is for possibly infinite sum, this is why you get the extra <code>Summability</code>goal that requires you to show the sum converges.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>okay. so in other words, <code>tsum</code> is specifically for sums that are finite (basing this also on <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/InfiniteSum/Defs.html#Summable\">docs</a>), which is why I need to provide a proof that this sum is finite. do I have that right?</p>",
        "id": 562330331,
