    {
        "content": "<p>No, <code>tsum</code> is for possibly infinite sums that unconditionally converge. They can converge to infinity if they are for example in the type ENNReal (the extended non-negative Reals which is <code>[0,∞]</code>)</p>",
        "id": 562330575,
        "sender_full_name": "David Ledvinka",
        "timestamp": 1765136967
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>okay. so would I edit my first statement to instead be this?:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><code>tsum</code> is specifically for sums that <em>converge</em>, which is why I need to provide a proof that this sum <em>converges</em>.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 562330667,
        "sender_full_name": "Becker A.",
        "timestamp": 1765137088
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ohhhhhh so it's to exclude things like the alternating series <code>[1, -1, 1, -1, ...]</code></p>",
